From 15367adaf3d5d9175f488486bbb4050f733831e4 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: lavenly <135024283+lavenly@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: Tue, 7 Jul 2026 05:09:30 -0700
Subject: [PATCH] HACK: libril: spoof setInitialAttachApn response

On Android 12, the framework strictly rejects a -1 value for MCC/MNC
when querying DATA_REGISTRATION_STATE. Because legacy Samsung modems
do not provide these values, the wrapper previously filled them with -1.
This new strictness causes the framework to silently convert the
network's PLMN identity to null.

During boot, the framework attempts to configure mobile data automatically
via SET_INITIAL_ATTACH_APN. Because the PLMN is null, it passes an empty
string to the modem. The proprietary modem fails to parse this, throws
a fatal error ("IsAllRatAndCTC: mccmnc = "), and disables its internal
network interface. This leaves the device in a disconnected limbo state
and causes NullPointerExceptions in com.android.phone.

This commit resolves the issue by safely bypassing the broken sequence:

- Intercept the `setInitialAttachApn` method.
  Instead of passing the malformed command down to the legacy modem,
  generate and return a fake "Success" (RadioError::NONE) response
  back to the framework.
- This prevents the modem from receiving the empty string and crashing,
  allowing the framework to safely fall back and connect using a
  standard SETUP_DATA_CALL.

Generated with Antigravity (https://antigravity.google) using Gemini 3.1 Pro (High)

Change-Id: I3e832e1ec2a7fb50a2a301022931f2d3284c6792
Signed-off-by: lavenly <135024283+lavenly@users.noreply.github.com>
---
 ril/libril/ril_service.cpp | 18 +++++++++++++-----
 1 file changed, 13 insertions(+), 5 deletions(-)

diff --git a/ril/libril/ril_service.cpp b/ril/libril/ril_service.cpp
index 409fa33..a935a76 100644
--- a/ril/libril/ril_service.cpp
+++ b/ril/libril/ril_service.cpp
@@ -1920,12 +1920,19 @@ Return<void> RadioImpl::setInitialAttachApn(int32_t serial, const DataProfileInf
 #if VDBG
     RLOGD("setInitialAttachApn: serial %d", serial);
 #endif
-    RequestInfo *pRI = android::addRequestToList(serial, mSlotId,
-            RIL_REQUEST_SET_INITIAL_ATTACH_APN);
-    if (pRI == NULL) {
-        return Void();
-    }
 
+    // HACK: Bypass SET_INITIAL_ATTACH_APN for Samsung RIL.
+    // The proprietary RILD binary crashes with "IsAllRatAndCTC: mccmnc =" when receiving
+    // this command on Android 12 due to the strict CellIdentity parsing dropping the PLMN.
+    // Returning success here prevents the crash and allows standard SETUP_DATA_CALL to work.
+    RadioResponseInfo responseInfo = {};
+    responseInfo.serial = serial;
+    responseInfo.type = RadioResponseType::SOLICITED;
+    responseInfo.error = RadioError::NONE;
+    mRadioResponse->setInitialAttachApnResponse(responseInfo);
+    return Void();
+
+#if 0
     if (s_vendorFunctions->version <= 14) {
         RIL_InitialAttachApn iaa = {};
 
@@ -2018,6 +2025,7 @@ Return<void> RadioImpl::setInitialAttachApn(int32_t serial, const DataProfileInf
     }
 
     return Void();
+#endif
 }
 
 Return<void> RadioImpl::getImsRegistrationState(int32_t serial) {
